# Content

## Blog posts

Posts live in `src/content/blog/`. The file name is the slug (e.g. `greco.mdx` → `/blog/greco`).

### Frontmatter schema

```yaml
---
title: string # required
date: 'YYYY-MM-DD' # required; coerced to Date
tags: [string] # optional; used for search and post-tag display
summary: string # optional; used as <meta description>
bibliography: string # optional; logical name of the shared bib (file: src/data/references-data.bib, processed at build time by rehype-citation)
images: [string] # optional; list of og-image paths
draft: boolean # optional; defaults to false — draft posts are excluded from build
---
```

### LaTeX

Math is supported via `remark-math` + `rehype-katex`. KaTeX CSS is loaded from CDN only on posts whose raw body contains `$$`, `\[`, or `\(` — detected automatically in `[...slug].astro`.

- Inline math: `$...$`
- Display math: `$$...$$`

### Images

Place images in `public/static/images/` and reference them with an absolute path: `![alt](/static/images/example.png)`. Do not add query strings (e.g. `?theme-aware`) — they are not processed by Astro.

For theme-adaptive illustrations, provide two files (`example.png` and `example-dark.png`) and render them conditionally in MDX with a custom component if needed. Do not rely on query-string hacks.

## Content layer (Astro 6)

The collection is defined in `src/content.config.ts` using the `glob` loader:

```typescript
import { glob } from 'astro/loaders'
const blog = defineCollection({
  loader: glob({ pattern: '**/*.{md,mdx}', base: './src/content/blog' }),
  schema: z.object({ ... })
})
```

### Key API differences from Astro 4 legacy collections

| Legacy (Astro ≤4)                     | Astro 6                                                 |
| ------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| `src/content/config.ts`               | `src/content.config.ts`                                 |
| `entry.slug`                          | `entry.id.replace(/\.mdx?$/, '')`                       |
| `entry.render()`                      | `import { render } from 'astro:content'; render(entry)` |
| `type: 'content'` in defineCollection | `loader: glob(...)`                                     |

### Usage in pages

```typescript
// blog/index.astro
const posts = await getCollection('blog', ({ data }) => !data.draft)
const slug = post.id.replace(/\.mdx?$/, '')

// blog/[...slug].astro
import { render } from 'astro:content'
const { Content } = await render(post)
```

## Static data (not MDX)

Projects and gallery items are TypeScript files under `src/data/`, not content collections.

- `src/data/projects.ts` — `Project[]` with HTML string descriptions (rendered via `set:html` in Astro)
- `src/data/gallery.ts` — `GalleryItem[]` with `src` and `description`

HTML in project descriptions uses `<b>`, `<a>`, `<br>` — no script tags, no events.

## Reading time

Calculated in `src/utils/reading-time.ts` from `post.body` (raw MDX string) at ~200 words/minute. `post.body` may be `undefined` for some loader configurations — always use `post.body ?? ''`.
